cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with self localization of wireless nodes using UWB radios and IEEE-standardized protocols. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as self localization is an important aspect of robotics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes an algorithm for clock error mitigation. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with measurement models and estimation algorithms. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is less likely but still relevant as the paper deals with localization of multiple nodes.
